    {
      "lineNumber": 1,
      "text": "Office Memorandum • UNITED STATES GOVERNMENT",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 2,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 3,
      "text": "TO      : Director, FBI",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 4,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 5,
      "text": "FROM    : SAC, San Antonio",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 6,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 7,
      "text": "SUBJECT: PROTECTION OF VITAL INSTALLATIONS",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 8,
      "text": "(Bureau file 65-48300)",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "text": "DATE: April 4, 1949",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "text": "AIR MAIL",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "text": "SPECIAL DELIVERY",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "text": "Reference is made to San Antonio letter to the Bureau dated March",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "22, 1949 which submitted information related by military authorities concerning",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "text": "unconventional aircraft.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "text": "The Office of the Assistant Chief of Staff, G-2, 4th Army, has advised",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "text": "that at 11:50 P.M. March 31, 1949 a lighted object about the size of a basketball,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "reddish white in color, followed by a fire trail, was observed southwest of",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "text": "Killeen Base, adjacent to Camp Hood, Texas. The observation was made by 1st",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "text": "Lt. FREDERICK D. DAVIS, who was in charge of a platoon, Company C, 12th Armored",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "text": "Infantry Battalion, which is assigned as a part of an alert force (called force",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "text": "Abel) from Camp Hood, whose function is to protect the installation at Killeen",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "text": "Base.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "text": "Lt. DAVIS advised that the object was at an altitude estimated at",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "6,000 ft., was traveling parallel to the ground and passed directly over him at",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "text": "a rapid rate of speed. It was in view 10 to 15 seconds and suddenly disappeared",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 31,
      "text": "high in the sky without having descended. No sound or odor was detected. The",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 32,
      "text": "night was clear and visibility good. The object passed almost directly over the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 33,
      "text": "air strip at Killeen Base.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 34,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 35,
      "text": "When Lt. DAVIS attempted to advise his headquarters by telephone",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 36,
      "text": "immediately after the sighting, he heard static or electrical interference on",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 37,
      "text": "the telephone line which he stated might be possible radio interference..",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 38,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 39,
      "text": "G-2 has advised that other lights of unknown origin were observed on",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 40,
      "text": "March 6, 7, 8 and 17, 1949, by military personnel of the alert force stationed",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 41,
      "text": "approximately 1000 yards east of the fences which surround Killeen Base.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 42,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 43,
      "text": "The object sighted on March 31, 1949 was reported as being of a",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 44,
      "text": "different nature from the lights seen earlier in the month.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 45,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 46,
      "text": "It is noted that Mr. WALTER WINCHELL, on his Sunday evening broadcast,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 47,
      "text": "April 3, 1949, stated that \"flying discs\" seen in this country definitely",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 48,
      "text": "emanated from Russia.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 49,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 50,
      "text": "On April 4, 1949, G-2, 4th Army, contacted this office, inquiring as",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 51,
      "text": "to whether we had any information that would substantiate or discredit the state-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 52,
      "text": "ments made by WALTER WINCHELL.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 53,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 54,
      "text": "2 cc - El Paso (100-4562)",
